The paper focuses on the development of an autonomous flight control system for UAVs in unstructured outdoor environments, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO). The proposed approach involves using machine learning techniques for navigation and exploration, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of regression-based learning also implies a connection to machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the application of the approach to UAV flight control suggests a connection to control systems (cs.SY).
